<div id="node-27" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/27" title="Of Persistence and POJOs: Bridging the Object and Relational Worlds">Of Persistence and POJOs: Bridging the Object and Relational Worlds</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Colin Sampaleanu on Mon, 2005-01-31 08:00        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_6 first last active"><a href="/presentations" rel="tag" title="A link to a technical article about Spring" class="active">Technical Article</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    Oracle
Technology Network features
an article titled &quot;Of Persistence and POJOs: Bridging the Object and
Relational Worlds&quot; by Rod Johnson and Jim Clark.&nbsp; This is an
article in the &quot;<span class="boldbodycopy">Mastering
J2EE Application Development Series&quot;.&nbsp; Read the ar</span>ticle
            <a href="http://www.oracle.com/technology/pub/articles/masterj2ee/j2ee_wk9.html">here</a>  </div>

